{"title_page": "Zirc District", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Zirc District\n| native_name            = <small>''Zirci j\u00e1r\u00e1s''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image_flag           = \n|image_blank_emblem   = Coa Hungary Town Zirc.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Zirci j\u00e1r\u00e1s.png\n|map_caption          = Zirc District within Hungary and Veszpr\u00e9m County. \n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Veszpr\u00e9m County|Veszpr\u00e9m]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Zirc]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_offset             = \n| timezone_DST           = \n| utc_offset_DST         = \n| coordinates            = \n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 331.02\n| area_rank              = [[Veszpr\u00e9m County#Regional structure|6th in Veszpr\u00e9m]]\n|population_footnotes    = \n|population_as_of        = 2011 census\n|population_total        = 19,386\n|population_rank         = [[Veszpr\u00e9m County#Regional structure|8th in Veszpr\u00e9m]]\n|population_density_km2  = 59\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Zirc''' ({{lang-hu|Zirci j\u00e1r\u00e1s}}) is a district in north-eastern part of [[Veszpr\u00e9m County]]. ''[[Zirc]]'' is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. The district is located in the [[Central Transdanubia|Central Transdanubia Statistical Region]].\n\n== Geography ==\nZirc District borders with [[Pannonhalma District]]  ''([[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County]])'' and [[Kisb\u00e9r District]] ''([[Kom\u00e1rom-Esztergom County]])'' to the north, [[M\u00f3r District]] ''([[Fej\u00e9r County]])'' and [[V\u00e1rpalota District]] to the east, [[Veszpr\u00e9m District]] to the south, [[P\u00e1pa District]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Zirc District is '''15'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''1''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|town]] and '''14''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2013)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2013.xls A KSH 2013. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Bakonyb\u00e9l]] (1,264)\n*[[Bakonyn\u00e1na]] (1,067)\n*[[Bakonyoszlop]] (441)\n*[[Bakonyszentkir\u00e1ly]] (867)\n*[[Borzav\u00e1r]] (723)\n*[[Csesznek]] (564)\n*[[Cset\u00e9ny]] (1,922)\n*[[Dudar]] (1,643)\n*[[L\u00f3k\u00fat]] (411)\n*[[Nagyeszterg\u00e1r]] (1,196)\n*[[Olaszfalu]] (1,061)\n*[[P\u00e9nzesgy\u0151r]] (332)\n*[[Porva]] (435)\n*[[Sz\u00e1p\u00e1r]] (485)\n*'''[[Zirc]]''' (7,106) \u2013 district seat\n}}\nThe '''bolded''' municipality is city.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of cities and towns in Hungary]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.iranyitoszamnavigator.hu/zirci-jaras-telepulesei Postal codes of the Zirc District]\n\n{{Zirc District}}\n{{Districts of Veszpr\u00e9m County}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Districts in Veszpr\u00e9m County]]\n\n\n{{Veszprem-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| name                   = Zirc District\n| native_name            = <small>''Zirci j\u00e1r\u00e1s''</small>\n| native_name_lang       = hu\n| settlement_type        = [[Districts of Hungary]]\n|image_flag           = \n|image_blank_emblem   = Coa Hungary Town Zirc.svg\n|blank_emblem_type    = Coat of arms\n|image_map            = Zirci j\u00e1r\u00e1s.png\n|map_caption          = Zirc District within Hungary and Veszpr\u00e9m County. \n| subdivision_type       = [[Countries of the world|Country]]\n| subdivision_name       = {{HUN}}\n| subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Hungary|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Veszpr\u00e9m County|Veszpr\u00e9m]]\n| seat_type              = District seat\n| seat                   = [[Zirc]]\n| timezone               = \n| utc_offset             = \n| timezone_DST           = \n| utc_offset_DST         = \n| coordinates            = \n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 331.02\n| area_rank              = [[Veszpr\u00e9m County#Regional structure|6th in Veszpr\u00e9m]]\n|population_footnotes    = \n|population_as_of        = 2011 census\n|population_total        = 19,386\n|population_rank         = [[Veszpr\u00e9m County#Regional structure|8th in Veszpr\u00e9m]]\n|population_density_km2  = 59\n| website                = \n}}\n'''Zirc''' ({{lang-hu|Zirci j\u00e1r\u00e1s}}) is a district in north-eastern part of [[Veszpr\u00e9m County]]. ''[[Zirc]]'' is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. The district is located in the [[Central Transdanubia|Central Transdanubia Statistical Region]].\n\n== Geography ==\nZirc District borders with [[Pannonhalma District]]  ''([[Gy\u0151r-Moson-Sopron County]])'' and [[Kisb\u00e9r District]] ''([[Kom\u00e1rom-Esztergom County]])'' to the north, [[M\u00f3r District]] ''([[Fej\u00e9r County]])'' and [[V\u00e1rpalota District]] to the east, [[Veszpr\u00e9m District]] to the south, [[P\u00e1pa District]] to the west. The number of the inhabited places in Zirc District is '''15'''.\n\n== Municipalities ==\nThe district has '''1''' [[List of cities and towns of Hungary|town]] and '''14''' villages.\n(ordered by population, as of 1 January 2013)<ref>[http://www.ksh.hu/docs/hun/hnk/hnk_2013.xls A KSH 2013. \u00e9vi helys\u00e9gn\u00e9vk\u00f6nyve]</ref>\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n*[[Bakonyb\u00e9l]] (1,264)\n*[[Bakonyn\u00e1na]] (1,067)\n*[[Bakonyoszlop]] (441)\n*[[Bakonyszentkir\u00e1ly]] (867)\n*[[Borzav\u00e1r]] (7