e.ie/eng/services/news/newsfeatures/covid19-updates/ COVID-19 updates] from the [[Health Service Executive]] (HSE)\n* [https://twitter.com/McConnellDaniel/status/1234176646686609415/photo/1 Letter sent to parents of those attending Scoil Chaitr\u00edona]\n* [https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0321/1124605-retired-gp-coronavirus/ \"Retired GP joins battle against Covid-19: 'I want to come back and help people'\"]. [[RT\u00c9 News]]. 22 March 2020.\n* [https://www.independent.ie/irish-news/stay-indoors-im-young-sporty-and-fit-i-never-would-have-thought-id-catch-coronavirus-39070693.html 'Stay indoors, I'm young, sporty and fit, I never would have thought I'd catch coronavirus']. ''[[Irish Independent]]''. 24 March 2020.\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Republic of Ireland| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Ireland]]\n[[Category:2020 in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Ireland]]\n[[Category:Disease-related deaths in the Republic of Ireland]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Ireland]]\n", "name_user": "Bygmester", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_the_Republic_of_Ireland"}
{"title_page": "Phalcon (framework)", "text_new": "{{Infobox software\n| name                   = Phalcon\n| logo                   =\n| logo_alt               = Phalcon Framework Logo\n| screenshot             = \n| caption                = \n| developer              = Andres Gutierrez and others\n| released               = {{release date|2012|11|14}}<ref>{{Cite web\n | url = https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/releases/tag/phalcon-v0.4.5\n | title = Release Version 0.4.5 \u00b7 phalcon/cphalcon\n | date = 2012-11-14 | accessdate = 2015-03-09\n | website   = github.com\n}}</ref>\n| latest release version = <!-- If you update this, remember to also update [[Comparison of web application frameworks]]--> 4.0.5\n| latest release date    = {{start date and age|2020|03|07|df=yes}}<ref name=\"phalcon_releasev4\">{{cite web | url=https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/releases/tag/v4.0.5 | title=Release Version 4.0.5 \u00b7 phalcon/cphalcon | publisher=github.com | date = 2020-01-25 | accessdate = 2020-01-25}}</ref>\n| latest preview date    = {{start date and age|2019|12|21|df=yes}}<ref name=\"phalcon_release\">{{cite web | url=https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/releases/tag/v4.0.0| title=Release Version 4.0.0 \u00b7 phalcon/cphalcon | publisher=github.com | date = 2019-12-21| accessdate = 2019-12-21}}</ref>\n| operating system       = \n| platform               = [[Unix]], [[Linux]], [[Mac OS&nbsp;X]], [[Windows]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://phalcon.io/en-us/download|title=Download Phalcon for Linux/Unix/Mac|work=phalcon.io}}</ref>\n| language               = \n| programming language   = [[Zephir (programming language)|Zephir]], [[C (programming language)|C]], [[PHP]]\n| license                = [[BSD License]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/blob/master/docs/LICENSE.md|title=cphalcon/LICENSE.md at master \u00b7 phalcon/cphalcon \u00b7 GitHub|work=GitHub}}</ref>\n| genre                  = [[Web application framework]]\n| website                = {{URL|http://phalcon.io/en-us/}}\n| repo                   = {{URL|https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon|Phalcon Repository}}\n| latest preview version = 4.0.0\n}}\n\n'''Phalcon''' is a [[PHP]] [[web framework]] based on the [[model\u2013view\u2013controller]] (MVC) [[Architectural pattern|pattern]].  Originally released in 2012, it is an [[Open-source software|open-source]] framework licensed under the terms of the [[BSD License]].\n\nUnlike most PHP frameworks, Phalcon is implemented as a [[web server]] [[Plug-in (computing)|extension]] written in [[Zephir (programming language)|Zephir]] and [[C (programming language)|C]], aiming to boost execution speed, reduce resource usage, and handle more [[HTTP request]]s per second than comparable frameworks written primarily in PHP.  One drawback of this approach is that [[Superuser|root/administrative]] access is required on the server to install Phalcon by building a custom binary or using a precompiled one.<ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://systemsarchitect.net/is-phalcon-the-promised-land-for-php/\n | title = Is Phalcon the promised land for PHP?\n | date = 2013-05-09 | accessdate = 2015-03-14\n | author = Lukasz Kujawa | website = systemsarchitect.net\n}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nPhalcon was created by Andr\u00e9s Guti\u00e9rrez and collaborators looking for a new approach to traditional web application frameworks written in PHP. The original draft of the framework in 2011 was called \"Spark\",<ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://phalcon.io/interview-with-phalconphp-creator-andres-guitierrez\n | title = Interview with PhalconPHP Creator Andr\u00e9s Guti\u00e9rrez\n | date = 2015-05-19 | accessdate = 2015-05-23\n | website = phalcon.io\n}}</ref> the name was later changed to Phalcon, representing the words \"PHP\" and \"[[falcon]]\".  Phalcon's initial release was made available on November 14, 2012.\n\nPhalcon&nbsp;0.3.5 includes an [[Object-relational mapping|ORM]] written in C, MVC components, and cache components. This release was followed by the Phalcon&nbsp;0.5.0 that brought a high-level dialect of [[SQL]] called PHQL, and Phalcon&nbsp;0.6.0 that introduced Volt, a template engine similar to [[Jinja (template engine)|Jinja]]. Phalcon 1.0 was released on March 22, 2013.<ref>{{cite web\n | url = https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/blob/master/CHANGELOG-1.x.md#100-2013-03-22\n | title = CHANGELOG-1.x.md at master\n | date = 2017-08-06 | accessdate   =2018-12-19\n | website = github.com\n}}</ref> with Phalcon 1.3 being the last minor release in that series.  Phalcon 2.0 saw most of the project ported from C to Zephir.\n\nPhalcon 3.0.0 was released on 29 July 2016,<ref>{{cite web\n | url = https://blog.phalcon.io/post/phalcon-3-0-0-released\n | title = Phalcon 3.0.0 released - Phalcon Framework\n | date = 2016-07-29 | accessdate   =2016-07-29\n | website = phalcon.io\n}}</ref> this major release includes support for PHP 7 as well as being Phalcon's first LTS (Long Term Support) release. Phalcon also adopted SemVer for their next releases versioning.\n\nPhalcon 4.0.0 was released on 21 December 2019,<ref>{{cite web\n | url = https://blog.phalcon.io/post/phalcon-4-0-0-released\n | title = Phalcon 4.0.0 released - Phalcon Framework\n | date = 2019-12-21 | accessdate   =2019-12-21\n | website = phalcon.io\n}}</ref> this major release includes support for PHP 7.2, 7.3 and 7.4 has Stricter Interfaces and support PSR-3, PSR-7, PSR-11 (proxy), PSR-13, PSR-16, PSR-17.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Zephir (programming language)]]\n* [[Phalcon Slayer]]{{snd}} a wrapper that restructures the Phalcon framework\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|https://phalcon.io}}\n* {{Official documentation|https://docs.phalcon.io}}\n* {{Discord Server|https://phalcon.io/discord}}\n* {{Official forum|https://forum.phalcon.io}}\n* {{Telegram|https://t.me/phalcon_news}}\n* {{Gab|https://phalcon.io/gab}}\n* {{MeWe|https://phalcon.io/mewe}}\n* {{Reddit|https://phalcon.io/reddit}}\n* {{Facebook|https://phalcon.io/fb}}\n* {{Twitter|https://phalcon.io/t}}\n* {{BitChute|https://phalcon.io/bitchute}}\n* {{Brighteon|https://phalcon.io/brighteon}}\n* {{LBRY|https://phalcon.io/lbry}}\n* {{YouTube|https://phalcon.io/youtube}}\n\n{{PHP}}\n{{Web frameworks}}\n\n[[Category:PHP frameworks]]\n[[Category:Software using the BSD license]]\n\n\n{{Web-software-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox software\n| name                   = Phalcon\n| logo                   =\n| logo_alt               = Phalcon Framework Logo\n| screenshot             = \n| caption                = \n| developer              = Andres Gutierrez and others\n| released               = {{release date|2012|11|14}}<ref>{{Cite web\n | url = https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/releases/tag/phalcon-v0.4.5\n | title = Release Version 0.4.5 \u00b7 phalcon/cphalcon\n | date = 2012-11-14 | accessdate = 2015-03-09\n | website   = github.com\n}}</ref>\n| latest release version = <!-- If you update this, remember to also update [[Comparison of web application frameworks]]--> 4.0.5\n| latest release date    = {{start date and age|2020|03|07|df=yes}}<ref name=\"phalcon_releasev4\">{{cite web | url=https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/releases/tag/v4.0.5 | title=Release Version 4.0.5 \u00b7 phalcon/cphalcon | publisher=github.com | date = 2020-01-25 | accessdate = 2020-01-25}}</ref>\n| latest preview date    = {{start date and age|2019|12|21|df=yes}}<ref name=\"phalcon_release\">{{cite web | url=https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/releases/tag/v4.0.0| title=Release Version 4.0.0 \u00b7 phalcon/cphalcon | publisher=github.com | date = 2019-12-21| accessdate = 2019-12-21}}</ref>\n| operating system       = \n| platform               = [[Unix]], [[Linux]], [[Mac OS&nbsp;X]], [[Windows]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://phalcon.io/en-us/download|title=Download Phalcon for Linux/Unix/Mac|work=phalcon.io}}</ref>\n| language               = \n| programming language   = [[Zephir (programming language)|Zephir]], [[C (programming language)|C]], [[PHP]]\n| license                = [[BSD License]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/blob/master/docs/LICENSE.md|title=cphalcon/LICENSE.md at master \u00b7 phalcon/cphalcon \u00b7 GitHub|work=GitHub}}</ref>\n| genre                  = [[Web application framework]]\n| website                = {{URL|http://phalcon.io/en-us/}}\n| repo                   = {{URL|https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon|Phalcon Repository}}\n| latest preview version = 4.0.0\n}}\n\n'''Phalcon''' is a [[PHP]] [[web framework]] based on the [[model\u2013view\u2013controller]] (MVC) [[Architectural pattern|pattern]].  Originally released in 2012, it is an [[Open-source software|open-source]] framework licensed under the terms of the [[BSD License]].\n\nUnlike most PHP frameworks, Phalcon is implemented as a [[web server]] [[Plug-in (computing)|extension]] written in [[Zephir (programming language)|Zephir]] and [[C (programming language)|C]], aiming to boost execution speed, reduce resource usage, and handle more [[HTTP request]]s per second than comparable frameworks written primarily in PHP.  One drawback of this approach is that [[Superuser|root/administrative]] access is required on the server to install Phalcon by building a custom binary or using a precompiled one.<ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://systemsarchitect.net/is-phalcon-the-promised-land-for-php/\n | title = Is Phalcon the promised land for PHP?\n | date = 2013-05-09 | accessdate = 2015-03-14\n | author = Lukasz Kujawa | website = systemsarchitect.net\n}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nPhalcon was created by Andr\u00e9s Guti\u00e9rrez and collaborators looking for a new approach to traditional web application frameworks written in PHP. The original draft of the framework in 2011 was called \"Spark\",<ref>{{cite web\n | url = http://phalcon.io/interview-with-phalconphp-creator-andres-guitierrez\n | title = Interview with PhalconPHP Creator Andr\u00e9s Guti\u00e9rrez\n | date = 2015-05-19 | accessdate = 2015-05-23\n | website = phalcon.io\n}}</ref> the name was later changed to Phalcon, representing the words \"PHP\" and \"[[falcon]]\".  Phalcon's initial release was made available on November 14, 2012.\n\nPhalcon&nbsp;0.3.5 includes an [[Object-relational mapping|ORM]] written in C, MVC components, and cache components. This release was followed by the Phalcon&nbsp;0.5.0 that brought a high-level dialect of [[SQL]] called PHQL, and Phalcon&nbsp;0.6.0 that introduced Volt, a template engine similar to [[Jinja (template engine)|Jinja]]. Phalcon 1.0 was released on March 22, 2013.<ref>{{cite web\n | url = https://github.com/phalcon/cphalcon/blob/master/CHANGELOG-1.x.md#100-2013-03-22\n | title = CHANGELOG-1.x.md at master\n | date = 2017-08-06 | accessdate   =2018-12-19\n | website = github.com\n}}</ref> with Phalcon 1.3 being the last minor release in that series.  Phalcon 2.0 saw most of the project ported from C to Zephir.\n\nPhalcon 3.0.0 was released on 29 July 2016,<ref>{{cite web\n | url = https://blog.phalcon.io/post/phalcon-3-0-0-released\n | title = Phalcon 3.0.0 released - Phalcon Framework\n | date = 2016-07-29 | accessdate   =2016-07-29\n | website = phalcon.io\n}}</ref> this major release includes support for PHP 7 as well as being Phalcon's first LTS (Long Term Support) release. Phalcon also adopted SemVer for their next releases versioning.\n\nPhalcon 4.0.0 was released on 21 December 2019,<ref>{{cite web\n | url = https://blog.phalcon.io/post/phalcon-4-0-0-released\n | title = Phalcon 4.0.0 released - Phalcon Framework\n | date = 2019-12-21 | accessdate   =2019-12-21\n | website = phalcon.io\n}}</ref> this major release includes support for PHP 7.2, 7.3 and 7.4 has Stricter Interfaces and support PSR-3, PSR-7, PSR-11 (proxy), PSR-13, PSR-16, PSR-17.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Zephir (programming language)]]\n* [[Phalcon Slayer]]{{snd}} a wrapper that restructures the Phalcon framework\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Offi